</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ullorianlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llorian Lanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/6/01 6:35:14 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanter Topic - managing groups.</span><hr size=1> Actually Ulaian you brought up a very good point i negelcted..<br>
<br>
I will re emphasize it here...<br>
<br>
Whenever you are moving camps ( Single groupm raid, whatever ), You NEVER, EVER, EVER pass your puller.  I cant stress this enough.  It is your PULLERS job to get you to the next camp site safely.  Dont take it upon yourself that it is time to move, ALWAYS check with your puller.<br>
<br>
Request that your puller inform you when it is time to move on the way to camp.  For example, in sebilis, you buff in the entrance and are sitting on the ramp ready to go.  Everyone else starts to run down the ramp after the puller... I sit and say &quot; XXXX(puller's name) can you let us know when its time to move ? Im sitting (yyyyy) (Y= previous camp spot).  <br>
<br>
Most people in your group will find out YOU the enchanter is not with them, and will turn around and come back to wherever you are.<br>
<br>
Another thing that i forgot to say is, Camp is usually where your puller tells you it is.  There are various camp spots usually for any particular &quot; camp&quot; and just because &quot;THIS&quot; puller wants to set up someplace different than what you are used to, doesnt make them wrong.  Each puller should have a pull &quot; pattern&quot; in their head, depending on where they like to stop on the way to camp, and pull once you get to camp.  You want your puller in his comfort zone, and you can mezz whevever he puts you, so camp to you, the enchanter shouldnt matter.<br>
<br>
Another thing, it is helpful if your puller tells you an approximate number of mobs inc ( as the 2 posters above mention ).  It doesnt have to be an exact number, but, somthing along the lines of &quot; here comes a bunch !!&quot; helps a lot, because you then have time to swap out spells if you need to while the pull is INC to camp ( such as AoE mezz if you dont keep this one memmed normally, etc ).<br>
<br>
Last thing, about moving to camps... The instruction for the group to stay where the puller puts them doesnt usually apply to rogues in the 50+ game.  Rogues are your scouters, and might know the dungeon better than even the puller.  I never worry when i dont see my rogue around, because i assume they are either scouting, or hide / sneaking .<br>
