</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvoidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Voidy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/6/01 6:54:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanter Topic - managing groups.</span><hr size=1> Regarding haste,  i time mine.  I have a piece of paper and a pen,  i'll write the time i cast aq,  then what the time will be in 20minutes.  I find that helps managing mana a lot.  4 aq's is around 40m.  And i generally dont like to dip below 50m.  So i will watch the time,  and i know i have to get to 90m before the haste wears off.<br>
<br>
In Seb,  there are heaps of casters to tot,  its not hard to haste 4 tanks, slow everything, do a lot of cc work and still have extra mana.  Other camps like karnors basement,  its much harder,  and i have to really conserve it.<br>
<br>
Staying between 50m - 90m is important i think,  I want to be able to have enough to cc -anything- the puller brings back.  A few times i have seen some random unexpected stuff happen,  like someone has forgot to snare etc, and we have ended up with close to 10 mobs.  If i wasnt at 80-90 mana, i would have gone oom before we finished even with tot.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts,  laters ;)<br>
