<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> In Seb, there are heaps of casters to tot, its not hard to haste 4 tanks, slow everything, do a lot of cc work and still have extra mana. Other camps like karnors basement, its much harder, and i have to really conserve it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Just a question really, in a camp like Karnors Basement where there are approximately 0 caster mobs, would it be of help to the enchanter if the puller brought down a low lvl casting mob (like a spectral caller) for him to keep perma-mezzed and ToT to gain extra mana? I do not know enough to myself determine if this would mean the enchanter had more mana due to being able to ToT, or less due to having to re-mezz all the time... help please <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Ulaian Moonleaf <BR>
