Leader, Avatars of Night</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ullorianlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llorian Lanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/6/01 8:23:33 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanter Topic - managing groups.</span><hr size=1> Yes if your group is sharp enough to allow you to do this, it helps a TON.<br>
<br>
We only have to mezz the mob 1 time every 96 seconds , and i think it cost about 125 mana.  Even if you cant sit to med ( are standing the entire time.. 2 mezzes is 250 mana, and ToT returns about 400 mana every 3 minutes unless the mob partially resists it.<br>
<br>
This rarely occurs ( shrooms partially resist, and other 55+ mobs, but this is rare ).<br>
<br>
C2 Returns 11 mana a tick even if we are not sitting so, at 10 ticks a minute, you are getting 110 mana back standing.  C2 returns the mana back from the mezz, so casting the mez on that one mob is basically free, even if you are standing.<br>
<br>
Most groups wont let you do this, but if you find one that will it is a HUGE help in a camp where caster mobs are infrequent.<br>
<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.mithrilweb.com//"target="web"><img src="http://www.mithrilweb.com/images/sigs/llosig.jpg" border="0">

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uguurn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Guurn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/6/01 8:24:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanter Topic - managing groups.</span><hr size=1>    I agree with almost everything sadi here.  I will add, I will allow pulls to start when I'm at 40 if I'm in a place that has plenty o mobs to tap ( Hs or Seblis).  I have also been toying with the idea of using Augment on the puller instead of haste on broken spawns.  I first started thinking about it when I was on slow duty as well as mezz in disco one night.  Robyyn(sp?) of the BMC was pulling and she scolded me for mezzing single pulls.  Instead she would just tank for the ten seconds it took for the last one to die.  I didn't do it on her that night, but I was wondering, is there any real drawback to doing this?  It would improve the pullers ac and give them a pretty good haste that I can cast on my cycle.  I also keep Augment on the cleric in the group.<br>
<br>
   I also have a few rules for mana stressful situations.  If we are getting Lom as a group and stere are still a few mobs to kill in the camp as well as buffs starting to fade. (Never happens?   Ya  .. right) I will, of course, make sure the primary healer has clarity at all costs,  I will also make sure the primary tank has haste at all costs. The healer is obvious but the tank?  If he isn't able to keep taunt, we are screwed.<br>
<br>
                         Guurn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usthistor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sthis Tor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/6/01 9:00:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanter Topic - managing groups.</span><hr size=1> Another tactic to keep in mind when your getting low on mana as a group and there are several mobs to go.  Direct the tanks to go after the lowest level/easiest mobs first.  This has a couple benefits,<br>
<br>
1. You can usually kill these mobs faster which means less mana mezzing for the enchanter.<br>
2. You usually take less damage which means less mana used for the healing<br>
<br>
In most of the pickup groups I've been a part of the feeling is that you have to go after the hardest mobs first.  This just isn't the case.  Go after the mob that makes the most sense for the situation your in.  <br>
<br>
Another thing you can sometimes do when your getting low on mana.  Just keep the mobs mezzed until the healers have mana.  I can keep 3 mobs mezzed forever assuming no resists and keep them sleeping for a very very long time even with resists.  If the group needs to take a breather midstream just call a halt to the fighting.  A heads up tank will realize whats what and take a pause.<br>
<br>
We once had a near wipeout with a demi in fear.  The pull was two Amy knights and the demi.  By the end, only a couple necro pets, mage pet, and a charmed Amy were left tanking the demi heh.  We managed to kill it, then kept the two Amy's sleeping for 30+ minutes while the whole raid rezzed and buffed themselves.  <br>
<br>
Cheers!<br>
<br>
Sthis Tor, 42nd level Monk<br>
