Leader, Avatars of Night</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufrostfire01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Frostfire01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/6/01 1:17:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanter Topic - managing groups.</span><hr size=1> Keeping a mob specifically as a mana battery for ToT is not actually that simple...<br>
<br>
It may be cause I'm usually in tells with at least ONE person, if not two. Sometimes, this can be really distracting and I lose my internal clock on mez.<br>
<br>
I do have a digital watch within hand's reach at my computer desk, set to stopwatch mode, so I can time mez with a watch if I want to... the only problem with using this is, theoretically,  you'll have to keep watch nearly in hand for 3-4 hours. I have timed stuff on my watch before, only to forget I was timing it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I suppose this is more to do with YOU and how well you can keep track of an extra mob that will be mezzed for hours. It probably becomes second nature if you do it enough. I find it sort of...suspenseful though. For me, it's fun if occasionally you have to play very smart and alert, but draining if I have to do it for hours on end. I've proven my skills to myself many times before, all of these &quot;enchanter moments&quot; popping up, and it does feel very nice when you've just done something somewhat hard. My personal preference while exping is playing with as little things I have to keep track of at once.<br>
<br>
I would also consider keeping it for emergency use only. Camps like Karnor's hand room, I remember, is very low on caster mobs, and the fights there can be pretty hectic as an enchanter. Hands themselves have relatively high hp and that leaves a lot of time for things to go bad/respawn. It has happened to me on a number (small number, but still) of occasions that we got behind in the spawn, and since we never really split spawn usually, ended up with 3-4 hands up at once. I can see how it could be useful here, assuming you don't ToT it until you get into a situation like this (ie ToT will always be up until you need it)<br>
<br>
However, I lived through those situations without it. You don't have to be able to keep any situation mezzed forever. You just have to keep all the stuff mezzed until your cleric ooms and you have to evac out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I personally think it's more of a convenience than a necessity. I can't think of a time where it would've meant the difference between victory and wipeout. That doesn't mean it never will though.<br>
<br>
I lived for 51 levels before any mana drain type thing. If you find yourself lower on mana, take steps to change that. Llorian posted some good ideas, like not slowing a single pull mob if cleric is doing well in mana. Alter your play style slightly and you can alter mana levels in group.  <p><br><br>
